Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} and bring back to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the @egg noodle nest{2}.

Add the noodles and green beans to the pan of water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

> Run the noodles and veg under cold water to stop them sticking together and to keep the veg vibrant.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and pepper. Fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g} to the beef.

Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @teriyaki sauce{150%ml} to the beef.

Cook, stirring, until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the teriyaki noodles between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!